View onlySpecific columnsEverythingFine-grained <p><pre><code>editable = {}
</code></pre> Nothing can be changed — safest, read-only.</p> <p><pre><code>editable = { 'money', 'job' }
</code></pre> Only these columns are editable. Types are detected automatically (number vs. text) and validated server-side.</p> <p><pre><code>editable = 'all'
</code></pre> All columns except the <code>primaryKey</code>.</p> <p>Warning</p> <p>Powerful — anyone with <code>dbedit</code> can change every field. Use only for trusted high-rank admins.</p> <p><pre><code>editable = {
    money = { type = 'number', min = 0, max = 9999999 },
    job   = { type = 'string', maxLen = 50 },
}
</code></pre> Per-column rules with clamping/length limits.</p>
